{# ---- Kay block --------------------------------------------------------- #}
<section class="ff-section">
  <div class="ff-wrap ff-kay">
    <div class="ff-kay-portrait ff-photo-needed ff-rv">
      <span class="ff-ph-icon">{{ icoCamera | safe }}</span>
      <p class="ff-ph-lbl">Portrait to source</p>
      <p class="ff-ph-desc">Kay outdoors, natural light, warm and unposed. Not a clinical headshot.</p>
      <p class="ff-ph-path">team set, pending on the CDN</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ff-rv ff-d1">
      <p class="ff-eyebrow">Who you would work with</p>
      <p class="ff-kay-quote">You're not stuck because <em>something's wrong with you.</em></p>
      <div class="ff-kay-body">
        <p>I have spent over 30 years in rooms with people who are anxious, and the pattern is almost always the same. They are trying hard, and the trying is not working. So we stop pushing and get curious instead. What is the alarm protecting? When does it fire? What happens if we let it ring without obeying it?</p>
        <p>That is usually where things start to shift. Not with a technique, and not overnight, but with two people looking at the thing together until it gets smaller.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ff-kay-sign">
        <span class="ff-kay-sign-name">Kay Wenger</span>
        <span class="ff-kay-sign-role">LMFT, LPCC, Founder</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

